            "author_association": "NONE",
            "body": "Just want to chime in and say that, having run into all the problems @HiPhish describes with a German keyboard layout, I have had to resort to the kind of system level remapping @ZyX-I describes (possible in OS X, albeit not out of the box, you have to install [Karabiner](https://pqrs.org/osx/karabiner/)).\n\nMy key takeaway from all that was that `langmap` is near useless for such usage cases (I’d even say it is terminally broken, but who am I to judge what the designed intent of a Vim feature was?). Fixing that sounds like a worthy goal for Neovim to me.\n",
