            "author_association": "NONE",
            "body": "Thanks for bringing up this issue. I've come across this problem many years ago when I was learning Dvorak. In the end, I've realized, that I can quite easily switch between different layouts, because the vim abbreviations are usually bound to the semantics of commands, but not the key placement.\n\nOn the other hand, there are still issues and that's why the project [ULKL](https://github.com/dumblob/ULKL) exists. It's actually like the solution mentioned in the first post - **Possible solution in Vim - fourth attempt**, but I wouldn't say it's a hack. Because it's a general issue, not (Neo)Vim-specific.\n",
