            "author_association": "NONE",
            "body": "There's a comment in the code to skip langmap if the key is mapped.... I was trying to work on changing things so that langmap comes first (which makes sense to me.... I'm using a non-standard keyboard layout (German Neo2) langmapped to english so that in normal mode (at least) I use the keys that were deliberately chosen to be easy to work with. I just don't know why <C-r> for example doesn't use the same key as r does). Comment [getchar.c:2003](https://github.com/neovim/neovim/blob/848fc8ede84b9cfc4e651e0e3b449060a8a8d70c/src/nvim/getchar.c#L2003)):\r\n// Skip \":lmap\" mappings if keys were mapped. \r\n\r\nAlso I'm worried because it's obviously a breaking change for possibly many users.... maybe it would require a switch between resolving langmap before resolving the mapping ??",
